ch.lambdaj.proxy

Class ProxyIterator<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.lambdaj.proxy.InvocationInterceptor
      • ch.lambdaj.proxy.ProxyIterator<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, InvocationHandler, net.sf.cglib.proxy.Callback, net.sf.cglib.proxy.MethodInterceptor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ProxyAggregator

    public class ProxyIterator<T>
extends InvocationInterceptor
implements Iterable<T>
    Proxies a list of objects in order to seamlessly iterate on them by exposing the API of a single object.
    Author:
    Mario Fusco, Mattias Jiderhamn, adding ability to disable or enable

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      protected boolean enabled
      Set to true (default) the interceptor will work on the proxiedIterator, if set to false it will ignore any method invocations.
